# Local API (Vite dev server proxies /api here)
VITE_API_PROXY_TARGET=http://127.0.0.1:5096

# Microsoft Entra ID (Azure AD) — required for production-style auth.
# Prefer a gitignored `.env.local` for real values (see `*.local` in .gitignore). Never put a client secret in any VITE_* variable.
# Omit all of these for local dev when the API uses AzureAd:DisableAuthentication (appsettings.Development.json).
# VITE_AZURE_CLIENT_ID = SPA app registration (public client) Application (client) ID
# VITE_AZURE_TENANT_ID = Directory (tenant) ID, or "common" for multi-tenant (not recommended for internal tools)
# VITE_AZURE_API_SCOPE = delegated scope exposed by the API app, e.g. api://<api-client-id>/access_as_user
# VITE_AZURE_REDIRECT_URI = SPA URL (defaults to window.location.origin)
# VITE_AZURE_POST_LOGOUT_REDIRECT_URI = optional; defaults to origin
# VITE_AZURE_CLIENT_ID=
# VITE_AZURE_TENANT_ID=
# VITE_AZURE_API_SCOPE=
# VITE_AZURE_REDIRECT_URI=https://your-frontend.azurewebsites.net
# VITE_AZURE_POST_LOGOUT_REDIRECT_URI=https://your-frontend.azurewebsites.net
